TEXT.1: This is the re-processed version of the MEA data archive from the CRRES spacecraft.

TEXT.2: The raw data provided by Principal Investigator A. Vampola have been processed to derive 1 min average data.

TEXT.3: The data consists of counting rates from 17 energy channels in the range of 0.1-2 MeV and 19 pitch angle bins at 1 minute time intervals.

TEXT.4: The average flux, 90 degree flux and N value are included.

TEXT.5: Also included are the spacecraft geographic coordinates and altitude, L shell, and the local and equatorial magnetic field magnitudes from the 1977 Olson-Pfitzer model of the earth's geomagnetic field.

TEXT.6: The raw high resolution (0.512 sec) data and documentation of raw data can be found at: https://spdf.gsfc.nasa.gov/pub/data/crres/particle_mea/

VarAttributes.FIELDNAM: Variance of 90 degree MEA flux at 148 keV
